  "text": "The Content Security Policy enforcement infrastructure in Firefox is implemented across multiple files in dom/security/ and dom/interfaces/security/. The nsCSPParser class (nsCSPParser.h/cpp) is the CSP directive parser that parses Content Security Policy header values into internal policy structures. It provides the static method parseContentSecurityPolicy() which tokenizes and parses a policy string according to CSP specifications. The nsCSPContext class (nsCSPContext.h/cpp) implements the main CSP context that holds and manages CSP policies for a document. It inherits from nsIContentSecurityPolicy and provides methods for policy enforcement and violation reporting, including GetAllowsInline() at line 637 which evaluates whether inline scripts are allowed by checking nonce, hash, and strict-dynamic sources. The nsCSPUtils.h/cpp files define utility functions and constants for CSP enforcement, including logging functions like CSP_LogLocalizedStr and violation observer topics. The nsIContentSecurityPolicy XPCOM interface is declared in dom/interfaces/security/nsIContentSecurityPolicy.idl and defines the scriptable interface that other components use to interact with CSP contexts. The inline script evaluation happens in nsCSPContext::GetAllowsInline() (lines 637-750+) which implements the CSP matching algorithm for inline scripts per the W3C spec, checking nonces, hashes, strict-dynamic, and unsafe-inline sources. Violation reporting is coordinated through nsCSPContext::AsyncReportViolation() which constructs violation events and sends them to observers and report endpoints."
}

